pageContext.claim: “And if you read the article [about the FBI's counterintelligence investigation], you'd see that they found absolutely nothing. But the headline of that article, it's called "The failing New York Times" for a reason, they've gotten me wrong for three years.”
pageContext.analysis: The {New York Times story} lays out the reasoning and groundwork for why the FBI opened a counterintelligence investigation. It does not specify any conclusions the FBI may or may not have drawn. The investigation was turned over to special counsel Robert S. Mueller's office when he was appointed. Mueller has yet to publicly release the findings of his investigation.
